##
## Filters for tests that fail only in MSAN builds on Linux
##
## When adding a new filter to this list, please include a short description of
## why the filter is required and create an associated tracking issue.
##

# Upstream Chromium test. Stable upstream (0.2% flake rate over 30 days per
# LUCI Analysis). The recorder panel has heavy initialization (~20 module
# imports, LitElement setup, extension system) that, combined with Brave's
# additional DevTools startup overhead (chromium_src overrides, NTP/stats
# services), exceeds the test's hardcoded 20-second timeout under MSAN
# instrumentation.
# https://github.com/brave/brave-browser/issues/53812
-DevToolsTest.TestShowRecorderTab

# Upstream Chromium test. Stable upstream (0.9% flake rate over 30 days per
# LUCI Analysis). The test performs 10 eval retries with exponentially
# increasing timeouts (total ~10s wall-clock). Combined with Brave's DevTools
# startup overhead (chromium_src overrides, NTP/stats services), this exceeds
# the hardcoded 20-second timeout under MSAN instrumentation. The sibling test
# CantInspectBlockedSubdomainHost is already disabled in the upstream source
# for the same reason.
# https://github.com/brave/brave-browser/issues/54053
-DevToolsExtensionHostsPolicyTest.CantInspectBlockedHost
